I looked at a bunch of other reviews for this game but barely any of the bad ones seem logical. Ive seen one where the person said it gets bad finger tracking. Thats not the games fault (as 90% have not had this issue) it is a problem with your phone. Ive seen one where they gave it a 2 star because they got a headache. Yes i did not mis-type, a headache made this person give it a 2 star. Im confused when people say they deleted the game because they died at the 5th stage and they had to restart, the stages take literally 3 seconds so it would take 15 seconds to get back to stage 5 :/ Each level contains 5 stages. Its not a bad game, its all opinion based, I personally enjoy games like these(quick reaction times, planning on where to jump and when), hence the 5 star, but i understand if its not some peoples cup of tea.

It TRIES to be a fast-paced platformer, but suffers from very slow controls. You have to drag your little dude from platform to platform in order to rescue your comrades from the big bad. But you have to LITERALLY drag him from platform to platform, and you're timed the entire time in each level. And it is a VERY short time. Some are as short as 2 seconds and the dragging is so sluggish, it just FEELS like a slow game. But the absolute worst part about this game? Every time you jump from platform to platform, the camera zooms in for absolutely no reason, making it EXTREMELY difficult to time all your moves correctly. If the camera wasn't so hyper, I would probably still be playing the game. But it's so sluggish and inaccurate with the dragging of the character, it's not worth the 82 MB in your phone
